{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-tamcon-lottery-api",
    "name": "Tamcon Lottery API",
    "description": "# Tamcon Weekly Lottery API\n\nBase URL: `{{baseUrl}}` · Health: `{{host}}/health`\n\n## Quick test flow\n\n1. **Create account** (new users) or ensure email exists in MongoDB `users`\n2. **Request OTP** → copy 6-digit code from server terminal `[OTP] email → code`\n3. **Verify OTP** → saves `accessToken` + `refreshToken` (check Postman Console)\n4. **Me** → confirm `role` is `admin` or `customer`\n5. **Admin KPIs** → requires `role: admin` (use `npm run promote-admin -- email`)\n6. **Create checkout** → open `checkoutUrl` in browser to pay (Chapa test mode)\n\n## Variables\n\n| Variable | Purpose |\n|----------|----------|\n| `email` | Login / register email |\n| `accessToken` | Set automatically by **Verify OTP** |\n| `drawId` | Set by **List draws** (admin) |\n| `chapaTxRef` | Set by **Create checkout** |\n\n## Auth\n\nCollection uses **Bearer** `{{accessToken}}`. Public routes override with **No Auth**.\n\n## Chapa\n\n- Webhook secret optional in dev; payments work via **callback** after checkout.\n- Docs: https://developer.chapa.co/dashboard/quick-start",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{accessToken}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "host", "value": "http://localhost:4000" },
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:4000/api/v1" },
    { "key": "email", "value": "aberamohammed19@gmail.com" },
    { "key": "accessToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "refreshToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "drawId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "chapaTxRef", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "System",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{host}}/health",
            "description": "No authentication required."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "description": "OTP login only. Email must exist in `users` (register first or insert in Atlas).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Create account (register)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"fullName\": \"Test User\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/register",
            "description": "Creates `role: customer`. Returns 409 if email already exists."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "2. Request OTP",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/otp/request",
            "description": "OTP is printed in the API server terminal. Response includes `role` and `fullName` if user exists."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "3. Verify OTP",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.code === 200);",
                  "try {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  const d = json && json.data;",
                  "  pm.test('Has accessToken', () => Boolean(d && d.accessToken));",
                  "  if (d && d.accessToken) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', d.accessToken);",
                  "    console.log('Saved accessToken — use Admin routes next');",
                  "  }",
                  "  if (d && d.refreshToken) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('refreshToken', d.refreshToken);",
                  "  }",
                  "  if (d && d.user) {",
                  "    console.log('Logged in as', d.user.email, 'role:', d.user.role);",
                  "  }",
                  "} catch (e) {",
                  "  console.error(e);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"otp\": \"000000\",\n  \"useHttpOnlyCookies\": false\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/otp/verify",
            "description": "Replace `otp` with the code from the server terminal. Always returns `accessToken` in JSON for Postman."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "4. Me (check token)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/me",
            "description": "Uses collection Bearer `{{accessToken}}`. Run after **Verify OTP**."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh session",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"refreshToken\": \"{{refreshToken}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh",
            "description": "Returns new tokens in JSON body."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/logout"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Lottery",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Current draw",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/lottery/current",
            "description": "Public. Returns active weekly draw and ticket price."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "My tickets",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/lottery/tickets/mine?page=1&limit=20",
            "description": "Requires login (Bearer token)."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Payments (Chapa)",
      "description": "Test mode keys in `.env`. After checkout, open `checkoutUrl` in a browser.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Chapa config (public key)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/payments/chapa/config",
            "description": "Returns Chapa public key and test/live mode."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create checkout",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 201', () => pm.response.code === 201);",
                  "try {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  const d = json && json.data;",
                  "  if (d && d.txRef) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('chapaTxRef', d.txRef);",
                  "    console.log('txRef:', d.txRef);",
                  "  }",
                  "  if (d && d.checkoutUrl) {",
                  "    console.log('Open checkoutUrl in browser:', d.checkoutUrl);",
                  "  }",
                  "} catch (e) {}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"quantity\": 1\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/payments/checkout",
            "description": "10 ETB per ticket. Response: `checkoutUrl`, `txRef`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Chapa callback (browser return)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/payments/chapa/callback?trx_ref={{chapaTxRef}}",
            "description": "Simulates Chapa redirect after payment. Uses `trx_ref` or `tx_ref` query param."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Admin",
      "description": "Requires `role: admin` on the logged-in user. Promote: `npm run promote-admin -- your@email.com`",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "KPIs",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/kpis",
            "description": "totalUsers, totalRevenue, ticketsSold, totalPrizePoolFromDraws, winnersCount, completedDraws"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "List all users",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/users?page=1&limit=50",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["admin", "users"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page", "value": "1" },
                { "key": "limit", "value": "50" },
                { "key": "role", "value": "admin", "disabled": true, "description": "customer | admin" },
                { "key": "search", "value": "", "disabled": true, "description": "Filter by email or fullName" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Paginated list of all users. Optional `role` and `search` query params."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Chart — revenue by week",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/charts/revenue-weeks"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Wallet transactions",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/transactions?page=1&limit=50",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["admin", "transactions"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page", "value": "1" },
                { "key": "limit", "value": "50" },
                { "key": "type", "value": "win_reward", "disabled": true, "description": "win_reward | ticket_purchase | adjustment" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "List draws",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "try {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  const first = json && json.data && json.data.items && json.data.items[0];",
                  "  if (first && first._id) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('drawId', first._id);",
                  "    console.log('drawId set to', first._id);",
                  "  }",
                  "} catch (e) {}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/draws?page=1&limit=50&status=open",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["admin", "draws"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page", "value": "1" },
                { "key": "limit", "value": "50" },
                { "key": "status", "value": "open", "disabled": true, "description": "open | completed" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Draw history",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/draws/history?page=1&limit=20"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Trigger weekly draw",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"drawId\": \"{{drawId}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/admin/draws/trigger",
            "description": "Run **List draws** first to set `drawId`. Closes draw and credits winners."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Chapa Webhook (optional)",
      "description": "Requires `CHAPA_WEBHOOK_SECRET` in `.env`. Optional in development.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Webhook — charge.success",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              {
                "key": "x-chapa-signature",
                "value": "<HMAC-SHA256 hex of raw body using CHAPA_WEBHOOK_SECRET>",
                "description": "Must match secret from Chapa Dashboard → Webhooks"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"event\": \"charge.success\",\n  \"status\": \"success\",\n  \"tx_ref\": \"{{chapaTxRef}}\",\n  \"amount\": \"10.00\",\n  \"currency\": \"ETB\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/payments/chapa/webhook"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
